{"title_page": "Vera Wang", "text_new": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox fashion designer\n| name = Vera Wang\n| image = Vera Wang.jpg\n| caption = Wang in 2007\n| nationality = American\n|birth_name=Vera Ellen Wang\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1949|6|27}}\n| birth_place = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| alma_mater = [[Sarah Lawrence College]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Arthur Becker]] <br />|1989|2012|end=separated}}\n| children = 2\n| label_name = Vera Ellen Wang\n| significant_design = \n| awards = [[Council of Fashion Designers of America|CFDA]]'s womenswear designer of the year, 2005; [[Andr\u00e9 Leon Talley]] Lifetime Achievement Award\n}}\n[[File:Vera Wang Spring-Summer 2014 04.jpg|thumb|Vera Wang Spring-Summer 2014 runway show at [[New York Fashion Week]]]]\n\n'''Vera Ellen Wang'''<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1989/06/23/style/vera-wang-wed-to-arthur-becker.html?pagewanted=1 \"Vera Wang Wed To Arthur Becker\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''. June 23, 1989. Retrieved April 23, 2010.</ref> ({{zh|c=\u738b\u8587\u8587}};<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/fashion/20140915/t15verawang/zh-hant/|title=\u8a2d\u8a08\u5e2b\u738b\u8587\u8587\u7684\u623f\u9593\uff0c\u90a3\u88e1\u4ec0\u9ebc\u90fd\u6c92\u6709|last=Friedman|first=Vanessa|date=2014-09-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-06-24|language=zh}}</ref> born June 27, 1949) is an American [[fashion designer]] based in [[New York City]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nVera Ellen Wang was born and  raised in New York City, and is of [[Han Chinese|Chinese]] descent. Her parents were born in China, and came to the United States in the mid-1940s. Her mother, Florence Wu (Wu Chifang), worked as a translator for the [[United Nations]], while her father, Cheng Ching Wang (Wang Chengqing), a graduate of [[Yanjing University]] and [[MIT]], owned a [[medicine]] company. Her maternal grandfather is [[Fengtian clique]] warlord [[Wu Junsheng]], who was killed by the [[Empire of Japan]] in the [[Huanggutun incident]] in 1928.<ref>http://www.5011.net/news/50203.html {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111165906/http://www.5011.net/news/50203.html |date=2018-01-11 }}{{quote needed|date=February 2019}}</ref>  Wang has one younger brother, Kenneth.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nWang attended [[Friends Seminary]],<ref name=\"Going\">{{cite news |title=Going Once, Going Twice |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/04/13/art-and-commerce-going-once-going-twice |accessdate=14 February 2019 |issue=April 13, 2015 |publisher=New Yorker Magazine}}</ref> graduated from [[The Chapin School (Manhattan)|The Chapin School]] in 1967, attended the [[University of Paris]] and earned a degree in [[art history]] from [[Sarah Lawrence College]]. Wang began [[figure skating]] at the age of eight.<ref name=nyt111220>{{cite news |url=https://tmagazine.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/12/20/vera-on-ice/ |title=Vera on Ice |first=Edward |last=Barsamian |work=The New York Times |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=December 20, 2011}}</ref> While in high school, she trained with [[pair skating|pairs]] partner James Stuart, and competed at the 1968 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]]. She was featured in ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'''s ''[[Faces in the Crowd (Sports Illustrated)|Faces in the Crowd]]'' in the January 9, 1968 issue.<ref>''[[Sports Illustrated]]'', December 15, 2006, p. 66</ref> When she failed to make the [[United States at the Olympics|U.S. Olympics]] team, she entered the fashion industry.<ref>{{cite book |title=Vera Wang (A&E Biography) |last=Krohn |first=Katherine |authorlink= |year=2006 |publisher=Twenty-First Century Books |location= |isbn=0-8225-6612-5 |page=112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xmJ7doZXP0QC}}</ref> Wang continues to enjoy skating, saying, \"Skating is multidimensional\".<ref name=nyt111220 />\n\nIn 1968, Wang was presented as a [[debutante]] to [[High society (social class)|high society]] at the [[International Debutante Ball]] at the [[Waldorf Astoria New York]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vera Wang: Enduring Style|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hd0PrIc9S3AC&pg=PA92&lpg=PA92&dq=vera+wang+international+debutante+ball&source=bl&ots=SNcW0F1zK0&sig=mVGSR6HJd8AAUsC6mSyYDi5YKPo&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUuv3YwrDYAhUHxiYKHXGoC38Q6AEIYDAL#v=onepage&q=vera%20wang%20international%20debutante%20ball&f=false|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nWang was hired to be an editor at [[Vogue (magazine)|''Vogue'']] immediately upon graduation from [[Sarah Lawrence College]], making her the youngest editor at that magazine. She stayed at ''Vogue'' for 17 years, leaving in 1987 to join [[Ralph Lauren]], for whom she worked for 2 years.  At 40 she resigned and became an independent bridal wear designer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/designers/verawang/ |title=Vera Wang |work=[[Fashion Model Directory]]}}</ref>\n\nWang has made wedding gowns for public figures such as [[Chelsea Clinton]],<ref name=vog12>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.vogue.com/946729/brides-who-wore-vera-wang-wedding-dresses |title=The 12 Most Stunning Vera Wang Brides |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=27 June 2014}}</ref> [[Karenna Gore]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/1997/07/12/gore.wedding |title=Gore's Eldest Daughter Weds New York Doctor In Washington |work=[[CNN]] |date=12 July 1997}}</ref> [[Ivanka Trump]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Campbell Brown (journalist)|Campbell Brown]],<ref>{{cite magazine |url= http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1179281,00.html |title=NBC's Campbell Brown Gets Married |magazine=[[People (American magazine)|People]] |date=2 April 2006}}</ref> [[Alicia Keys]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Mariah Carey]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Victoria Beckham]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]],<ref>http://celebritybrideguide.com/sarah-michelle-gellar-freddie-prinze-jr-wedding/</ref> [[Avril Lavigne]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Hilary Duff]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Khloe Kardashian]],<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/brides/gallery/2013101315041/Vera-wang-brides-celebrity-dresses/3/ |title=Celebrities who wore Vera Wang on their wedding day |magazine=[[Hello!]] |date=13 October 2013 |page=3}}</ref> and [[Kim Kardashian]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/brides/gallery/2013101315041/Vera-wang-brides-celebrity-dresses/4/ |title= Celebrities who wore Vera Wang on their wedding day |magazine=Hello! |date=13 October 2013 |page=4}}</ref>  Wang's evening wear has also been worn by [[Michelle Obama]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/insider/2011/12/05/michelle-obama-dons-vera-wang/ |title=Michelle Obama Dons Vera Wang |magazine=[[Elle Magazine]] |date=5 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120711150117/http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/insider/2011/12/05/michelle-obama-dons-vera-wang/ |archivedate=11 July 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.vogue.com/fashion/10-best-dressed/tis-the-season/ |title=Photos: 10 Best Dressed: Week of December 12, 2011 |magazine=Vogue |date=December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215171749/http://www.vogue.com/fashion/10-best-dressed/tis-the-season/ |archivedate=February 15, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nShe has designed costumes for [[Figure skating|figure skaters]], including [[Nancy Kerrigan]], [[Michelle Kwan]], [[Evan Lysacek]], [[Nathan Chen]]. Kerrigan wore Wang for the [[1992 Winter Olympics|1992]] and [[1994 Winter Olympics]], Kwan for the [[1998 Winter Olympics|1998]] and [[2002 Winter Olympics]], Lysacek for the [[2010 Winter Olympics]], and Chen for the [[2018 Winter Olympics]].<ref name=\"frey\">{{cite news| last1= Frey| first1= Kaitlyn |title=Vera Wang Reflects on More Than 20 Years of Designing Olympic Figure Skating Costumes |url=http://people.com/style/vera-wang-interview-design-figure-skating-costumes |accessdate=12 February 2018|work=People|date=8 February 2018}}</ref> Wang was inducted into the [[U.S. Figure Skating Hall of Fame]] in 2009 for her contribution to the sport as a costume designer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/2009-01-21-figure-skating-championships_N.htm |title=Johnny Weir, Evan Lysacek in battle at figure skating nationals |work=[[USA Today]] |date=22 January 2009}}</ref> She designed the uniforms worn by the [[Philadelphia Eagles Cheerleaders]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/cheerleaders/highlights.html |title=Highlights |work=[[Philadelphia Eagles]] |access-date=2016-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419025336/http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/cheerleaders/highlights.html |archive-date=2018-04-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn October 23, 2001, her book, ''Vera Wang on Weddings'', was released. In June 2005, she won the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America]] (CFDA) Womenswear Designer of the Year.  On May 27, 2006, Wang was awarded the [[Andr\u00e9 Leon Talley]] Lifetime Achievement Award from the [[Savannah College of Art and Design]].\n\nWang's evening wear has been worn by stars at many red carpet events, including [[Viola Davis]] at the 2012 Academy Awards,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-17174658 |title=Oscars 2012: Stars arrive |work=[[BBC News]] |date=27 February 2012 |at=Image 3 of 16}}</ref> and [[Sofia Vergara]] at the 65th Emmy Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/465262/sofia-vergara-reveals-she-ll-marry-in-a-cleavage-baring-vera-wang-get-all-the-details-on-her-fab-gown |title=Sof\u00eda Vergara Talks Wedding Dress: It Has to Be Vera Wang |work=[[E! News]] |date=2 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nShe was honored with the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America]] Lifetime Achievement Award in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/life_and_entertainment/2013/06/05/vera-wang-honored-for-lifetime-achievement.html |title=Vera Wang honored for lifetime achievement |work=[[The Columbus Dispatch]] |date=5 June 2013}}</ref><ref>cfda.com [https://cfda.com/members/profile/vera-wang \"Vera Wang\"], Council of Fashion Designers of America.</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Wang reached a deal with [[Kohl's]], a chain of department stores, to produce a less expensive line of ready-to-wear clothing exclusively for them called Simply Vera.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/vera-wang-9542398#commercial-success|title=Vera Wang - Fashion Designer - Biography |website=biography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-02-14}}</ref>\n\nForbes placed her the 34th in the list America's Richest Self-Made Women 2018, her revenues rising to $630 million in that year.\n\nOn September 10, 2019, after a sabbatical of 2 years during which she had presented her collections only via films,<ref>https://news.yahoo.com/vera-wang-returns-hippie-hair-214308733.html Article \"Vera Wang returns, with hippie hair and couture lingerie\" by Jocelyn Noveck</ref> Vera Wang returned to the [[New York Fashion Week]] runway for her Spring/Summer 2020 fashion show, which celebrated the 30th anniversary of her brand.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mkax-LFPxmQ Video of the complete show on YouTube</ref> The show got very positive reviews, Godfrey Deeny describing it as a \"notable collection by one of the few New York designers with a truly distinctive fashion DNA\",<ref>https://in.fashionnetwork.com/news/Vera-wang-soars-yet-stumbles,1135695.html Article \"Vera Wang soars yet stumbles\" by Godfrey Deeny on fashionnetwork.com</ref> while Bridget Foley presented Vera's creations as \"Beautiful, seriously designed clothes, presented with gutsy panache\".<ref>https://wwd.com/runway/spring-ready-to-wear-2020/new-york/vera-wang/review/ Vera Wang RTW Spring 2020, review by Bridget Foley</ref> However, the show was marred by several major footwear malfunctions,<ref name=\"Review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/11/style/proenza-schouler-gabriela-hearst-new-york-fashion-week.html \"Vera Wang [...] threw in shoes so acutely angled and vertiginous that her models\u2019 knees shook with the effort to remain upright. Two actually fell, and one limped down the runway with one shoe off and one on\", review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times</ref><ref>https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/spring-2020-ready-to-wear/vera-wang \"But the complications of her improbably willowy silhouette proved overwhelming elsewhere, and two models took spills from their sky-high platforms\", review by Nicole Phelps for vogue.com</ref> especially during the finale when no less than four models fell down,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sq4j6kR0IWY Video on YouTube</ref> including the showstopper, top model [[Fei Fei Sun]], who fell twice in a row,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y6AJf1s9rKE Video on YouTube</ref> leading chief fashion critic [[Vanessa Friedman]] to state that \"In 2019, no woman should be tortured by what she wears\".<ref name=\"Review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times\" />\n\n==Retail==\nIn 1990, she opened her own design salon in the [[Carlyle Hotel]] in [[New York City]] that features her trademark bridal gowns.<ref name=\"VeraWangFashionLines\">[https://nymag.com/fashion/fashionshows/designers/bios/verawang/ \"Vera Wang \u2013 Designer Fashion Label Biography\"], ''[[New York Magazine]]''. Retrieved October 20, 2009.</ref> She has since opened bridal boutiques in New York, London, Tokyo, and Sydney and has also expanded her brand through her fragrance,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.verawangfragrances.com |title=Vera Wang Fragrances |publisher=VeraWangFragrances.com |accessdate=April 13, 2015}}</ref> jewelry, eyewear, shoes, and homeware collections.\n\n\"White by Vera Wang\" launched on February 11, 2011, at [[David's Bridal]]. Prices of the bridal gowns range from $600 to $1,400 which gives more brides a more affordable way to wear Vera's designs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.davidsbridal.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/PressRoom_Davids-Bridal-White-by-Vera-Wang-Launches |title=White by Vera Wang launches at David's Bridal |publisher=David's Bridal |accessdate=2013-11-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130121081522/http://www.davidsbridal.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/PressRoom_Davids-Bridal-White-by-Vera-Wang-Launches |archivedate=2013-01-21 }}</ref> In 2002, Wang began to enter the home fashion industry and launched The Vera Wang China and Crystal Collection,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fashionxstyles.com/2014/11/vera-wang-bridal-pink-outfit-collection-by-audrey-hepburn |title=Pink Collection by Audrey Hepburn |accessdate=2014-11-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150224170249/http://www.fashionxstyles.com/2014/11/vera-wang-bridal-pink-outfit-collection-by-audrey-hepburn/ |archivedate=2015-02-24 }}</ref> followed by the 2007 release of her [[diffusion line]] called Simply Vera, which are sold exclusively by [[Kohl's]].<ref name=\"VeraWangFashionLines\" />\n\nIn Spring of 2012, Wang teamed up with [[Men's Wearhouse]] to offer two [[tuxedo]] styles available in both the retail and rental areas of their inventory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mens-wearhouse-partners-with-vera-wang-to-launch-black-by-vera-wang-135645733.html |website=PR Newswire |publisher=PR Newswire |accessdate=2015-05-18|title=Men's Wearhouse Partners with Vera Wang to Launch Black by Vera Wang }}</ref>\nIn June 2012, she expanded in [[Australia]] with the opening of \"Vera Wang Bride Sydney\" and her first Asian flagship store \"Vera Wang Bridal Korea\", helmed by President Jung Mi-ri, in upmarket neighborhood [[Cheongdam-dong]] in [[Gangnam-gu]], [[Seoul]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Lee |first=Rachel |title= Vera Wang opens 1st Asia flagship in Seoul |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2012/10/199_114120.html |accessdate=16 December 2012 |newspaper=Korea Times |date=29 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with a CBS reporter, Wang said, \"(It's) painful, and not only that, I have no choice. So I think when you start there's a certain innocence because of that freedom, and as you evolve you begin to see the parameters of what you can and can't do. So I make decisions that are very tiny that will affect an hour of work, I make decisions that will impact the lives of the people that work for me. It's in fashion as well, micro work, a centimeter of proportion and then it's macro to see what a vision is on the red carpet.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/vera-wang-talks-bridal-inspiration-how-she-applies-fashion-sense-to-wedding-style/|title=Vera Wang talks bridal inspiration, how she applies fashion sense to wedding style|access-date=2017-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1989, she married [[Arthur Becker]] in an [[Interfaith marriage|interfaith]] [[Baptist]] and [[Interfaith marriage in Judaism|Jewish ceremony]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1989/06/23/style/vera-wang-wed-to-arthur-becker.html \"Vera Wang Wed To Arthur Becker\"], ''New York Times'', June 23, 1989</ref><ref name=Todd>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=GMeeM3sc4pgC&pg=PA45&lpg=PA45&dq=vera+wang+adopted#v=onepage&q=adopted&f=false |title=Vera Wang |isbn=9781438100388 |last1=Todd |first1=Anne M. |year=2007 }}</ref> They resided in [[Manhattan, New York City|Manhattan]] with their two adopted daughters:<ref name=Todd /> Cecilia (born 1990), who currently lives in New York City, and Josephine (born 1993), who attended [[The Chapin School]] and currently attends [[Harvard University]]. Becker was the CEO of the information technology services company [[NaviSite]] until August 2010. In July 2012, Vera Wang Co. announced that the couple had separated. The separation was amicable.<ref name=dailymail20120711>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/11/vera-wang-arthur-becker-separate-_n_1664277.html |title=Vera Wang, Arthur Becker Separate After 23 Years Of Marriage |work=Huffington Post |date=July 11, 2012 |accessdate=July 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nVera Wang loves sports and exercise. She spends her day dealing with all the different lines of product she handles, from poring over china patterns to small leather goods at Kohl's. She usually doesn't take phone calls during the day.<ref name=\"My List: Vera Wang in 24 Hours\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/a910/24-hours-with-vera-wang-1112/|title=My List: Vera Wang in 24 Hours|date=2012-10-16|newspaper=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2017-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nSeveral movies and television shows have mentioned Wang's works.\n\nIn the ''[[Sex and the City]]'' TV series, [[Charlotte York Goldenblatt|Charlotte York]] found Wang's wedding dress to be the perfect wedding dress, and wore it for her wedding to Trey MacDougal.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rrOIWxT8mmIC |title=Sex and the City: Kiss and Tell |author=Amy Sohn|isbn=9780743457309 |date=2004-02-23 }}</ref> Wang's design was mentioned in the [[NBC]] television show ''[[The West Wing]]'' in the episode \"[[The Black Vera Wang]]\". In ABC's ''[[Ugly Betty]]'' TV series, Vera Wang makes a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]] as herself, designing a dress for Wilhelmina Slater's wedding to Bradford Meade.\n\nIn the film ''[[Sex and the City (film)|Sex and the City]]'', Vera Wang was among the bridal gowns [[Carrie Bradshaw]] wore in her ''Vogue'' photo shoot. In the film ''[[Bride Wars]]'', [[Anne Hathaway]] and [[Kate Hudson]] wore custom-made Vera Wang gowns.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.brides.com/wedding-dresses-style/wedding-dresses/editorial-pick/2009/01/ibride-warsi-style#slide=1 |title=Bride Wars Wedding Style |work=Brides}}</ref>\n\nIn the film ''[[Diary of a Mad Black Woman (film)|Diary of a Mad, Black Woman]]'', Madea rips a dress by Vera Wang, which surprises Brenda.\n\nIn the ''[[Totally Spies!]]'' episode \"The Wedding Crasher\", a villain named Wera Van (parody of Vera Wang), desires revenge on those who rejected her wedding dress designs.\n\nVera Wang also designed a wedding dress for [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]]'s character [[Buffy Summers]] in the TV Series ''[[Buffy The Vampire Slayer]]'' episode \"[[The Prom (Buffy the Vampire Slayer)|The Prom]]\".\n\nIn the TV series, ''[[How to Get Away with Murder]]'', the character [[Michaela Pratt]] mentioned a custom Vera Wang wedding gown when confronting her fianc\u00e9, [[Aiden Walker]], about his sexuality.\n\nIn the political comedy ''[[First Daughter (2004 film)|First Daughter]]'', Wang, playing herself, takes the president's daughter Samantha Mackenzie ([[Katie Holmes]]) and her friend Mia ([[Amerie]]) to try on wedding dresses. She is shown to have a close friendship with Mackenzie, cheek-kissing and grasping hands.\n\nIn the TV Series ''[[Gossip Girl]]'', Vera Wang is mentioned in multiple episodes and is one of [[Blair Waldorf]]'s favorite designers. Blair has a wedding dress designed by Vera Wang for her wedding to Prince Louis of Monaco. Blair decides she can no longer wear it after losing her and Louis's baby in a car accident, and has another designed instead. The three bridesmaids in Blair's wedding wear Vera Wang bridesmaid dresses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2085891/Vera-Wang-bridesmaid-dresses-Gossip-Girls-royal-wedding-sale-did-Blair-snap-blush-pink-ones.html |title =Vera Wang bridesmaid dresses from Gossip Girl's royal wedding go on sale (but did Blair snap up all the blush pink ones?) |work=Mail Online|date =2012-01-13 }}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=October 2019}}\n\nAlso in ''[[Revenge (TV series)|Revenge]]'', [[Victoria Grayson]], played by [[Madeleine Stowe]], wears a steel gray Vera Wang mermaid gown in her second wedding with [[Conrad Grayson]] ([[Henry Czerny]]). The dress was actually shown in black at Wang's Fall 2012 show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.instyle.com/news/revenge-first-look-victoria-graysons-vera-wang-wedding-dress |title=Revenge First Look: Victoria Grayson&#039;s Vera Wang Wedding Dress \u2013 InStyle.com |work=InStyle.com}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[Super Bowl LI|2017 Super Bowl]], [[Lady Gaga]] wore Vera Wang Spring/Summer 2017.\n\nIn the second-season episode of ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', \"Mr. & Mrs. Mxyzptlk\", Mr. Mxyzptlk snaps his fingers and puts a wedding dress on ''Supergirl''.  When she protests that he \"can't just put [her] in a wedding dress\", he responds, \"Why not?  It's Vera Wang\".\n\nSimilarly, in ''[[The Simpsons]]'' episode \"My Big Fat Geek Wedding\", Edna Krabappel walks out on her wedding to Seymour Skinner. Nelson Muntz refuses to egg her with a canola oil egg per Bart Simpson's request because the dress is a Vera Wang. He eggs Skinner with it instead.\n\nShe is mentioned in a film, ''[[The Accountant (2016 film)|The Accountant]]'', as the character Dana Cummings describes her as the designer of a dress that she coveted for her senior prom.\n\nShe is interviewed in a movie, \"[[Scatter My Ashes at Bergdorf's]]\", which chronicles the history of the famous department store in Manhattan.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n* ''[[First Daughter (2004 film)|First Daughter]]'' (2004) as herself.\n* ''[[The September Issue]]'' (2009) as herself.\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'' (2012) as herself.\n* ''[[Keeping Up with the Kardashians]] '' (2011) as herself.\n* ''[[Chelsea Lately]] '' (2011) as herself.\n* ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice]]'' (2008) as herself.\n* ''[[Ugly Betty]] '' (2007) as herself.\n\n==Books==\n* Vera Wang, ''Vera Wang on Weddings'', [[HarperCollins]], October 2001 ({{ISBN|9780688162566}}).\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|China|Fashion}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vera Wang}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.verawang.com}}\n* {{FMD designer|vera-wang}}\n* {{IMDb name|911056}}\n\n{{Geoffrey Beene Lifetime Achievement Award|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wang, Vera}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Chinese businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American company founders]]\n[[Category:American debutantes]]\n[[Category:American designers]]\n[[Category:American fashion businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from New York City]]\n[[Category:Chapin School (Manhattan) alumni]]\n[[Category:Chinese women company founders]]\n[[Category:Clothing brands of the United States]]\n[[Category:Debutantes of the International Debutante Ball]]\n[[Category:Dinnerware designers]]\n[[Category:High fashion brands]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Luxury brands]]\n[[Category:Sarah Lawrence College alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Paris alumni]]\n[[Category:Wedding dress designers]]\n[[Category:Women company founders]]\n[[Category:Friends Seminary alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-vandalism|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox fashion designer\n| name = Vera Wang\n| image = Vera Wang.jpg\n| caption = Wang in 2007\n| nationality = American\n|birth_name=Vera Ellen Wang\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1949|6|27}}\n| birth_place = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| alma_mater = [[Sarah Lawrence College]]\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Arthur Becker]] <br />|1989|2012|end=separated}}\n| children = 2\n| label_name = Vera Ellen Wang\n| significant_design = \n| awards = [[Council of Fashion Designers of America|CFDA]]'s womenswear designer of the year, 2005; [[Andr\u00e9 Leon Talley]] Lifetime Achievement Award\n}}\n[[File:Vera Wang Spring-Summer 2014 04.jpg|thumb|Vera Wang Spring-Summer 2014 runway show at [[New York Fashion Week]]]]\n\n'''Vera Ellen Wang'''<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1989/06/23/style/vera-wang-wed-to-arthur-becker.html?pagewanted=1 \"Vera Wang Wed To Arthur Becker\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''. June 23, 1989. Retrieved April 23, 2010.</ref> ({{zh|c=\u738b\u8587\u8587}};<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://cn.nytimes.com/fashion/20140915/t15verawang/zh-hant/|title=\u8a2d\u8a08\u5e2b\u738b\u8587\u8587\u7684\u623f\u9593\uff0c\u90a3\u88e1\u4ec0\u9ebc\u90fd\u6c92\u6709|last=Friedman|first=Vanessa|date=2014-09-15|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-06-24|language=zh}}</ref> born June 27, 1949) is an American [[fashion designer]] based in [[New York City]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nVera Ellen Wang was born and  raised in New York City, and is of [[Han Chinese|Chinese]] descent. Her parents were born in China, and came to the United States in the mid-1940s. Her mother, Florence Wu (Wu Chifang), worked as a translator for the [[United Nations]], while her father, Cheng Ching Wang (Wang Chengqing), a graduate of [[Yanjing University]] and [[MIT]], owned a [[medicine]] company. Her maternal grandfather is [[Fengtian clique]] warlord [[Wu Junsheng]], who was killed by the [[Empire of Japan]] in the [[Huanggutun incident]] in 1928.<ref>http://www.5011.net/news/50203.html {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180111165906/http://www.5011.net/news/50203.html |date=2018-01-11 }}{{quote needed|date=February 2019}}</ref>  Wang has one younger brother, Kenneth.{{citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\nWang attended [[Friends Seminary]],<ref name=\"Going\">{{cite news |title=Going Once, Going Twice |url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2015/04/13/art-and-commerce-going-once-going-twice |accessdate=14 February 2019 |issue=April 13, 2015 |publisher=New Yorker Magazine}}</ref> graduated from [[The Chapin School (Manhattan)|The Chapin School]] in 1967, attended the [[University of Paris]] and earned a degree in [[art history]] from [[Sarah Lawrence College]]. Wang began [[figure skating]] at the age of eight.<ref name=nyt111220>{{cite news |url=https://tmagazine.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/12/20/vera-on-ice/ |title=Vera on Ice |first=Edward |last=Barsamian |work=The New York Times |date=December 20, 2011 |accessdate=December 20, 2011}}</ref> While in high school, she trained with [[pair skating|pairs]] partner James Stuart, and competed at the 1968 [[U.S. Figure Skating Championships]]. She was featured in ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'''s ''[[Faces in the Crowd (Sports Illustrated)|Faces in the Crowd]]'' in the January 9, 1968 issue.<ref>''[[Sports Illustrated]]'', December 15, 2006, p. 66</ref> When she failed to make the [[United States at the Olympics|U.S. Olympics]] team, she entered the fashion industry.<ref>{{cite book |title=Vera Wang (A&E Biography) |last=Krohn |first=Katherine |authorlink= |year=2006 |publisher=Twenty-First Century Books |location= |isbn=0-8225-6612-5 |page=112 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xmJ7doZXP0QC}}</ref> Wang continues to enjoy skating, saying, \"Skating is multidimensional\".<ref name=nyt111220 />\n\nIn 1968, Wang was presented as a [[debutante]] to [[High society (social class)|high society]] at the [[International Debutante Ball]] at the [[Waldorf Astoria New York]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Vera Wang: Enduring Style|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hd0PrIc9S3AC&pg=PA92&lpg=PA92&dq=vera+wang+international+debutante+ball&source=bl&ots=SNcW0F1zK0&sig=mVGSR6HJd8AAUsC6mSyYDi5YKPo&hl=nl&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjUuv3YwrDYAhUHxiYKHXGoC38Q6AEIYDAL#v=onepage&q=vera%20wang%20international%20debutante%20ball&f=false|newspaper=USA Today|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nWang was hired to be an editor at [[Vogue (magazine)|''Vogue'']] immediately upon graduation from [[Sarah Lawrence College]], making her the youngest editor at that magazine. She stayed at ''Vogue'' for 17 years, leaving in 1987 to join [[Ralph Lauren]], for whom she worked for 2 years.  At 40 she resigned and became an independent bridal wear designer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/designers/verawang/ |title=Vera Wang |work=[[Fashion Model Directory]]}}</ref>\n\nWang has made wedding gowns for public figures such as [[Chelsea Clinton]],<ref name=vog12>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.vogue.com/946729/brides-who-wore-vera-wang-wedding-dresses |title=The 12 Most Stunning Vera Wang Brides |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |date=27 June 2014}}</ref> [[Karenna Gore]],<ref>{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/ALLPOLITICS/1997/07/12/gore.wedding |title=Gore's Eldest Daughter Weds New York Doctor In Washington |work=[[CNN]] |date=12 July 1997}}</ref> [[Ivanka Trump]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Campbell Brown (journalist)|Campbell Brown]],<ref>{{cite magazine |url= http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1179281,00.html |title=NBC's Campbell Brown Gets Married |magazine=[[People (American magazine)|People]] |date=2 April 2006}}</ref> [[Alicia Keys]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Mariah Carey]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Victoria Beckham]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]],<ref>http://celebritybrideguide.com/sarah-michelle-gellar-freddie-prinze-jr-wedding/</ref> [[Avril Lavigne]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Hilary Duff]],<ref name=vog12 /> [[Khloe Kardashian]],<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/brides/gallery/2013101315041/Vera-wang-brides-celebrity-dresses/3/ |title=Celebrities who wore Vera Wang on their wedding day |magazine=[[Hello!]] |date=13 October 2013 |page=3}}</ref> and [[Kim Kardashian]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.hellomagazine.com/brides/gallery/2013101315041/Vera-wang-brides-celebrity-dresses/4/ |title= Celebrities who wore Vera Wang on their wedding day |magazine=Hello! |date=13 October 2013 |page=4}}</ref>  Wang's evening wear has also been worn by [[Michelle Obama]].<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/insider/2011/12/05/michelle-obama-dons-vera-wang/ |title=Michelle Obama Dons Vera Wang |magazine=[[Elle Magazine]] |date=5 December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20120711150117/http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/insider/2011/12/05/michelle-obama-dons-vera-wang/ |archivedate=11 July 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.vogue.com/fashion/10-best-dressed/tis-the-season/ |title=Photos: 10 Best Dressed: Week of December 12, 2011 |magazine=Vogue |date=December 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215171749/http://www.vogue.com/fashion/10-best-dressed/tis-the-season/ |archivedate=February 15, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nShe has designed costumes for [[Figure skating|figure skaters]], including [[Nancy Kerrigan]], [[Michelle Kwan]], [[Evan Lysacek]], [[Nathan Chen]]. Kerrigan wore Wang for the [[1992 Winter Olympics|1992]] and [[1994 Winter Olympics]], Kwan for the [[1998 Winter Olympics|1998]] and [[2002 Winter Olympics]], Lysacek for the [[2010 Winter Olympics]], and Chen for the [[2018 Winter Olympics]].<ref name=\"frey\">{{cite news| last1= Frey| first1= Kaitlyn |title=Vera Wang Reflects on More Than 20 Years of Designing Olympic Figure Skating Costumes |url=http://people.com/style/vera-wang-interview-design-figure-skating-costumes |accessdate=12 February 2018|work=People|date=8 February 2018}}</ref> Wang was inducted into the [[U.S. Figure Skating Hall of Fame]] in 2009 for her contribution to the sport as a costume designer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/olympics/2009-01-21-figure-skating-championships_N.htm |title=Johnny Weir, Evan Lysacek in battle at figure skating nationals |work=[[USA Today]] |date=22 January 2009}}</ref> She designed the uniforms worn by the [[Philadelphia Eagles Cheerleaders]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/cheerleaders/highlights.html |title=Highlights |work=[[Philadelphia Eagles]] |access-date=2016-08-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180419025336/http://www.philadelphiaeagles.com/cheerleaders/highlights.html |archive-date=2018-04-19 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nOn October 23, 2001, her book, ''Vera Wang on Weddings'', was released. In June 2005, she won the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America]] (CFDA) Womenswear Designer of the Year.  On May 27, 2006, Wang was awarded the [[Andr\u00e9 Leon Talley]] Lifetime Achievement Award from the [[Savannah College of Art and Design]].\n\nWang's evening wear has been worn by stars at many red carpet events, including [[Viola Davis]] at the 2012 Academy Awards,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-17174658 |title=Oscars 2012: Stars arrive |work=[[BBC News]] |date=27 February 2012 |at=Image 3 of 16}}</ref> and [[Sofia Vergara]] at the 65th Emmy Awards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/465262/sofia-vergara-reveals-she-ll-marry-in-a-cleavage-baring-vera-wang-get-all-the-details-on-her-fab-gown |title=Sof\u00eda Vergara Talks Wedding Dress: It Has to Be Vera Wang |work=[[E! News]] |date=2 October 2013}}</ref>\n\nShe was honored with the [[Council of Fashion Designers of America]] Lifetime Achievement Award in 2013.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dispatch.com/content/stories/life_and_entertainment/2013/06/05/vera-wang-honored-for-lifetime-achievement.html |title=Vera Wang honored for lifetime achievement |work=[[The Columbus Dispatch]] |date=5 June 2013}}</ref><ref>cfda.com [https://cfda.com/members/profile/vera-wang \"Vera Wang\"], Council of Fashion Designers of America.</ref>\n\nIn 2006, Wang reached a deal with [[Kohl's]], a chain of department stores, to produce a less expensive line of ready-to-wear clothing exclusively for them called Simply Vera.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.biography.com/people/vera-wang-9542398#commercial-success|title=Vera Wang -\nFashion Designer - Biography |website=biography.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-02-14}}</ref>\n\nForbes placed her the 34th in the list America's Richest Self-Made Women 2018, her revenues rising to $630 million in that year.\n\nOn September 10, 2019, after a sabbatical of 2 years during which she had presented her collections only via films,<ref>https://news.yahoo.com/vera-wang-returns-hippie-hair-214308733.html Article \"Vera Wang returns, with hippie hair and couture lingerie\" by Jocelyn Noveck</ref> Vera Wang returned to the [[New York Fashion Week]] runway for her Spring/Summer 2020 fashion show, which celebrated the 30th anniversary of her brand.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mkax-LFPxmQ Video of the complete show on YouTube</ref> The show got very positive reviews, Godfrey Deeny describing it as a \"notable collection by one of the few New York designers with a truly distinctive fashion DNA\",<ref>https://in.fashionnetwork.com/news/Vera-wang-soars-yet-stumbles,1135695.html Article \"Vera Wang soars yet stumbles\" by Godfrey Deeny on fashionnetwork.com</ref> while Bridget Foley presented Vera's creations as \"Beautiful, seriously designed clothes, presented with gutsy panache\".<ref>https://wwd.com/runway/spring-ready-to-wear-2020/new-york/vera-wang/review/ Vera Wang RTW Spring 2020, review by Bridget Foley</ref> However, the show was marred by several major footwear malfunctions,<ref name=\"Review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times\">https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/11/style/proenza-schouler-gabriela-hearst-new-york-fashion-week.html \"Vera Wang [...] threw in shoes so acutely angled and vertiginous that her models\u2019 knees shook with the effort to remain upright. Two actually fell, and one limped down the runway with one shoe off and one on\", review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times</ref><ref>https://www.vogue.com/fashion-shows/spring-2020-ready-to-wear/vera-wang \"But the complications of her improbably willowy silhouette proved overwhelming elsewhere, and two models took spills from their sky-high platforms\", review by Nicole Phelps for vogue.com</ref> especially during the finale when no less than four models fell down,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sq4j6kR0IWY Video on YouTube</ref> including the showstopper, top model [[Fei Fei Sun]], who fell twice in a row,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y6AJf1s9rKE Video on YouTube</ref> leading chief fashion critic [[Vanessa Friedman]] to state that \"In 2019, no woman should be tortured by what she wears\".<ref name=\"Review by Vanessa Friedman for The New York Times\" />\n\n==Retail==\nIn 1990, she opened her own design salon in the [[Carlyle Hotel]] in [[New York City]] that features her trademark bridal gowns.<ref name=\"VeraWangFashionLines\">[https://nymag.com/fashion/fashionshows/designers/bios/verawang/ \"Vera Wang \u2013 Designer Fashion Label Biography\"], ''[[New York Magazine]]''. Retrieved October 20, 2009.</ref> She has since opened bridal boutiques in New York, London, Tokyo, and Sydney and has also expanded her brand through her fragrance,<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.verawangfragrances.com |title=Vera Wang Fragrances |publisher=VeraWangFragrances.com |accessdate=April 13, 2015}}</ref> jewelry, eyewear, shoes, and homeware collections.\n\n\"White by Vera Wang\" launched on February 11, 2011, at [[David's Bridal]]. Prices of the bridal gowns range from $600 to $1,400 which gives more brides a more affordable way to wear Vera's designs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.davidsbridal.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/PressRoom_Davids-Bridal-White-by-Vera-Wang-Launches |title=White by Vera Wang launches at David's Bridal |publisher=David's Bridal |accessdate=2013-11-23 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130121081522/http://www.davidsbridal.com/webapp/wcs/stores/servlet/PressRoom_Davids-Bridal-White-by-Vera-Wang-Launches |archivedate=2013-01-21 }}</ref> In 2002, Wang began to enter the home fashion industry and launched The Vera Wang China and Crystal Collection,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fashionxstyles.com/2014/11/vera-wang-bridal-pink-outfit-collection-by-audrey-hepburn |title=Pink Collection by Audrey Hepburn |accessdate=2014-11-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150224170249/http://www.fashionxstyles.com/2014/11/vera-wang-bridal-pink-outfit-collection-by-audrey-hepburn/ |archivedate=2015-02-24 }}</ref> followed by the 2007 release of her [[diffusion line]] called Simply Vera, which are sold exclusively by [[Kohl's]].<ref name=\"VeraWangFashionLines\" />\n\nIn Spring of 2012, Wang teamed up with [[Men's Wearhouse]] to offer two [[tuxedo]] styles available in both the retail and rental areas of their inventory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mens-wearhouse-partners-with-vera-wang-to-launch-black-by-vera-wang-135645733.html |website=PR Newswire |publisher=PR Newswire |accessdate=2015-05-18|title=Men's Wearhouse Partners with Vera Wang to Launch Black by Vera Wang }}</ref>\nIn June 2012, she expanded in [[Australia]] with the opening of \"Vera Wang Bride Sydney\" and her first Asian flagship store \"Vera Wang Bridal Korea\", helmed by President Jung Mi-ri, in upmarket neighborhood [[Cheongdam-dong]] in [[Gangnam-gu]], [[Seoul]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Lee |first=Rachel |title= Vera Wang opens 1st Asia flagship in Seoul |url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2012/10/199_114120.html |accessdate=16 December 2012 |newspaper=Korea Times |date=29 June 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with a CBS reporter, Wang said, \"(It's) painful, and not only that, I have no choice. So I think when you start there's a certain innocence because of that freedom, and as you evolve you begin to see the parameters of what you can and can't do. So I make decisions that are very tiny that will affect an hour of work, I make decisions that will impact the lives of the people that work for me. It's in fashion as well, micro work, a centimeter of proportion and then it's macro to see what a vision is on the red carpet.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/vera-wang-talks-bridal-inspiration-how-she-applies-fashion-sense-to-wedding-style/|title=Vera Wang talks bridal inspiration, how she applies fashion sense to wedding style|access-date=2017-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1989, she married [[Arthur Becker]] in an [[Interfaith marriage|interfaith]] [[Baptist]] and [[Interfaith marriage in Judaism|Jewish ceremony]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1989/06/23/style/vera-wang-wed-to-arthur-becker.html \"Vera Wang Wed To Arthur Becker\"], ''New York Times'', June 23, 1989</ref><ref name=Todd>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/?id=GMeeM3sc4pgC&pg=PA45&lpg=PA45&dq=vera+wang+adopted#v=onepage&q=adopted&f=false |title=Vera Wang |isbn=9781438100388 |last1=Todd |first1=Anne M. |year=2007 }}</ref> They resided in [[Manhattan, New York City|Manhattan]] with their two adopted daughters:<ref name=Todd /> Cecilia (born 1990), who currently lives in New York City, and Josephine (born 1993), who attended [[The Chapin School]] and currently attends [[Harvard University]]. Becker was the CEO of the information technology services company [[NaviSite]] until August 2010. In July 2012, Vera Wang Co. announced that the couple had separated. The separation was amicable.<ref name=dailymail20120711>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/07/11/vera-wang-arthur-becker-separate-_n_1664277.html |title=Vera Wang, Arthur Becker Separate After 23 Years Of Marriage |work=Huffington Post |date=July 11, 2012 |accessdate=July 11, 2012}}</ref>\n\nVera Wang loves sports and exercise. She spends her day dealing with all the different lines of product she handles, from poring over china patterns to small leather goods at Kohl's. She usually doesn't take phone calls during the day.<ref name=\"My List: Vera Wang in 24 Hours\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/designers/a910/24-hours-with-vera-wang-1112/|title=My List: Vera Wang in 24 Hours|date=2012-10-16|newspaper=Harper's BAZAAR|access-date=2017-02-14|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nSeveral movies and television shows have mentioned Wang's works.\n\nIn the ''[[Sex and the City]]'' TV series, [[Charlotte York Goldenblatt|Charlotte York]] found Wang's wedding dress to be the perfect wedding dress, and wore it for her wedding to Trey MacDougal.<ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rrOIWxT8mmIC |title=Sex and the City: Kiss and Tell |author=Amy Sohn|isbn=9780743457309 |date=2004-02-23 }}</ref> Wang's design was mentioned in the [[NBC]] television show ''[[The West Wing]]'' in the episode \"[[The Black Vera Wang]]\". In ABC's ''[[Ugly Betty]]'' TV series, Vera Wang makes a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]] as herself, designing a dress for Wilhelmina Slater's wedding to Bradford Meade.\n\nIn the film ''[[Sex and the City (film)|Sex and the City]]'', Vera Wang was among the bridal gowns [[Carrie Bradshaw]] wore in her ''Vogue'' photo shoot. In the film ''[[Bride Wars]]'', [[Anne Hathaway]] and [[Kate Hudson]] wore custom-made Vera Wang gowns.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.brides.com/wedding-dresses-style/wedding-dresses/editorial-pick/2009/01/ibride-warsi-style#slide=1 |title=Bride Wars Wedding Style |work=Brides}}</ref>\n\nIn the film ''[[Diary of a Mad Black Woman (film)|Diary of a Mad, Black Woman]]'', Madea rips a dress by Vera Wang, which surprises Brenda.\n\nIn the ''[[Totally Spies!]]'' episode \"The Wedding Crasher\", a villain named Wera Van (parody of Vera Wang), desires revenge on those who rejected her wedding dress designs.\n\nVera Wang also designed a wedding dress for [[Sarah Michelle Gellar]]'s character [[Buffy Summers]] in the TV Series ''[[Buffy The Vampire Slayer]]'' episode \"[[The Prom (Buffy the Vampire Slayer)|The Prom]]\".\n\nIn the TV series, ''[[How to Get Away with Murder]]'', the character [[Michaela Pratt]] mentioned a custom Vera Wang wedding gown when confronting her fianc\u00e9, [[Aiden Walker]], about his sexuality.\n\nIn the political comedy ''[[First Daughter (2004 film)|First Daughter]]'', Wang, playing herself, takes the president's daughter Samantha Mackenzie ([[Katie Holmes]]) and her friend Mia ([[Amerie]]) to try on wedding dresses. She is shown to have a close friendship with Mackenzie, cheek-kissing and grasping hands.\n\nIn the TV Series ''[[Gossip Girl]]'', Vera Wang is mentioned in multiple episodes and is one of [[Blair Waldorf]]'s favorite designers. Blair has a wedding dress designed by Vera Wang for her wedding to Prince Louis of Monaco. Blair decides she can no longer wear it after losing her and Louis's baby in a car accident, and has another designed instead. The three bridesmaids in Blair's wedding wear Vera Wang bridesmaid dresses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/femail/article-2085891/Vera-Wang-bridesmaid-dresses-Gossip-Girls-royal-wedding-sale-did-Blair-snap-blush-pink-ones.html |title =Vera Wang bridesmaid dresses from Gossip Girl's royal wedding go on sale (but did Blair snap up all the blush pink ones?) |work=Mail Online|date =2012-01-13 }}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=October 2019}}\n\nAlso in ''[[Revenge (TV series)|Revenge]]'', [[Victoria Grayson]], played by [[Madeleine Stowe]], wears a steel gray Vera Wang mermaid gown in her second wedding with [[Conrad Grayson]] ([[Henry Czerny]]). The dress was actually shown in black at Wang's Fall 2012 show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.instyle.com/news/revenge-first-look-victoria-graysons-vera-wang-wedding-dress |title=Revenge First Look: Victoria Grayson&#039;s Vera Wang Wedding Dress \u2013 InStyle.com |work=InStyle.com}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[Super Bowl LI|2017 Super Bowl]], [[Lady Gaga]] wore Vera Wang Spring/Summer 2017.\n\nIn the second-season episode of ''[[Supergirl (TV series)|Supergirl]]'', \"Mr. & Mrs. Mxyzptlk\", Mr. Mxyzptlk snaps his fingers and puts a wedding dress on ''Supergirl''.  When she protests that he \"can't just put [her] in a wedding dress\", he responds, \"Why not?  It's Vera Wang\".\n\nSimilarly, in ''[[The Simpsons]]'' episode \"My Big Fat Geek Wedding\", Edna Krabappel walks out on her wedding to Seymour Skinner. Nelson Muntz refuses to egg her with a canola oil egg per Bart Simpson's request because the dress is a Vera Wang. He eggs Skinner with it instead.\n\nShe is mentioned in a film, ''[[The Accountant (2016 film)|The Accountant]]'', as the character Dana Cummings describes her as the designer of a dress that she coveted for her senior prom.\n\nShe is interviewed in a movie, \"[[Scatter My Ashes at Bergdorf's]]\", which chronicles the history of the famous department store in Manhattan.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Movies===\n* ''[[First Daughter (2004 film)|First Daughter]]'' (2004) as herself.\n* ''[[The September Issue]]'' (2009) as herself.\n\n===Television===\n* ''[[Gossip Girl (TV series)|Gossip Girl]]'' (2012) as herself.\n* ''[[Keeping Up with the Kardashians]] '' (2011) as herself.\n* ''[[Chelsea Lately]] '' (2011) as herself.\n* ''[[The Celebrity Apprentice]]'' (2008) as herself.\n* ''[[Ugly Betty]] '' (2007) as herself.\n\n==Books==\n* Vera Wang, ''Vera Wang on Weddings'', [[HarperCollins]], October 2001 ({{ISBN|9780688162566}}).\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|China|Fashion}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Vera Wang}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.verawang.com}}\n* {{FMD designer|vera-wang}}\n* {{IMDb name|911056}}\n\n{{Geoffrey Beene Lifetime Achievement Award|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wang, Vera}}\n[[Category:1949 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century Chinese businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American company founders]]\n[[Category:American debutantes]]\n[[Category:American designers]]\n[[Category:American fashion businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers of Chinese descent]]\n[[Category:American fashion designers]]\n[[Category:Businesspeople from New York City]]\n[[Category:Chapin School (Manhattan) alumni]]\n[[Category:Chinese women company founders]]\n[[Category:Clothing brands of the United States]]\n[[Category:Debutantes of the International Debutante Ball]]\n[[Category:Dinnerware designers]]\n[[Category:High fashion brands]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Luxury brands]]\n[[Catego